articles.author: NAJIB JOBAIN and SAMY MAGDY
articles.description: RAFAH, Gaza Strip (AP) — Egypt is threatening to suspend its peace treaty with Israel if Israeli troops are sent into the densely populated Gaza border town of Rafah, where it says fighting could force the closure of the besieged territory's main aid supply route, two Egyptian officials and a Western diplomat said Sunday.
articles.title: Egypt threatens to suspend key peace treaty if Israel pushes into Rafah on its border, officials say

articles.author: The Associated Press
articles.description: JERUSALEM (AP) — The sound of gunfire crackled over the phone as the teenage girl hid in the car and spoke. An Israeli tank was near the vehicle as she and her family were trying to heed Israel’s call to evacuate their home in Gaza.
articles.title: 'They are shooting at us.' A fleeing Gaza family is killed along with the medics sent to find them

articles.author: JILL LAWLESS
articles.description: LONDON (AP) — As chances rise of a Joe Biden-Donald Trump rematch in the U.S. presidential election race, America’s allies are bracing for a bumpy ride.
articles.title: American allies worry the US is growing less dependable, whether Trump or Biden wins

articles.author: JILL COLVIN
articles.description: NEW YORK (AP) — Donald Trump said that, as president, he warned NATO allies that he “would encourage” Russia “to do whatever the hell they want” to countries that are “delinquent” as the front-runner for the Republican nomination ramped up his attacks on foreign aid and long-standing international alliances.
articles.title: Trump says he warned NATO ally: Spend more on defense or Russia can 'do whatever the hell they want'

articles.author: COLLEEN LONG
articles.description: WILMINGTON, Del. (AP) — First lady Jill Biden said in an email to campaign donors that she didn't know what the special counsel was trying to achieve when he suggested President Joe Biden could not remember when his son Beau died.
articles.title: First lady questions whether special counsel referenced son's death to score political points

articles.author: MARIA SHERMAN and FOSTER KLUG
articles.description: LOS ANGELES (AP) — Will she make it in time? Intrepid flight trackers online seem to think so.On social media, fans of Taylor Swift and aviation journalists believe they've identified Swift's private jet, labeled “The Football Era." It arrived from Tokyo’s Haneda Airport to Los Angeles' LAX airport just after 3:30 p.m.
articles.title: Taylor Swift reaches LAX in journey from Tokyo to Super Bowl, online sleuths say. Will she make it?

articles.description: KYIV, Ukraine (AP) — Russian forces launched 45 drones over Ukraine Sunday in a five-and-a-half-hour barrage, officials said, as Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy continued the reshuffle of his war cabinet as the war enters its third year.
articles.title: Russia launches 45 drones in mass barrage of Ukraine as Kyiv continues war cabinet reshuffle

articles.author: MICHAEL HILL
articles.description: ILION, N.Y. (AP) — Remington began here two centuries ago and generations of workers have turned out rifles and shotguns at the massive firearms factory in the middle of this blue-collar village in the heart of New York’s Mohawk Valley.
articles.title: This small New York village made guns for 200 years. What happens when Remington leaves?

articles.author: LINDSEY BAHR
articles.description: “ Lisa Frankenstein ” didn’t come to life at the North American box office in its first weekend in theaters.
articles.title: ‘Lisa Frankenstein’ fails to revive North American box office on a very slow Super Bowl weekend

articles.author: SPENCER RIPCHIK
articles.description: LAS VEGAS (AP) — Super Bowl ticket prices remain out of reach for many fans who made travel reservations months ago to come to Las Vegas this week, so they'll likely be watching on TV like millions of others.
articles.title: Pricey Super Bowl: Some NFL fans pass on expensive tickets and just have 'a good time' in Vegas
